## Accessing the spool set indexes and file configuration mode
- In the **Output settings exploration **panel, click on **File and metadata**.

- Click the **Details **button against the configuration you wish to access.

Or:

- In the **Output settings exploration **panel, click on the name of the required file and metadata setting.

- Click **spool sets settings **to access the configuration of the spool set indexes.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

## Changing the processing lot subdivision mode
The subdivision mode sets the relationship between processing lots and spool sets. You may choose the subdivision mode from those described below:

**Name**

**Description**

**Single delivery lot**

All processing lots are conveyed to the same spool set. You must specify one file and metadata setting for the single lot.

**A delivery lot for each processing lot**

Each processing lot is conveyed to a different spool set. You must specify one file and metadata setting for each spool set.

- Access the spool set indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Select **one spool set for each lot**.

- In the confirmation prompt window, click **Apply **to apply the change.

### Switching to one spool set for each lot and viceversa
When switching to a spool set per lot configuration, a spool set is created for each lot, and removed when its corresponding lot is deleted. Each lot will use its associated spool set configurations. The user must configure all spool sets.

When switching from a multiple spool set configuration to a single spool set configuration, only one of the existing spool sets is preserved and the others are discarded. The user can choose which spool set to preserve. All existing lots will use the same spool set configuration.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Changing the properties of a spool set
- Access the spool set indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click the name of the spool set whose properties you wish to modify or **Single lot **if you have only one spool set.

- Drag a String type attribute into the **Path **box.

- Drag a String type attribute into the **Index path **box.

- Choose the print mode of the pages from **all pages **and **only front pages.**

- Select a spool set separation mode (the separation mode indicates the conditions under which the spool set will be subdivided into more than one file) from the **Break the file **menu:

**Never (Keep the spool set together) **

- **Every shipment**

- **Every envelope **

- **Every document**

- If you have selected **Limit file size to**, enter the number of pages to be used as the subdivision point.

> **Valid from Digital Archiving 3 - 3.15.0**

In order to optimize the download time and compression rate of a single document for the multi-document PDF format, it is recommended not to exceed the maximum size of 7MB for the resulting multi-document PDF.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

### Spool file settings
This panel allows to generate extra pages to position the first page of a shipment on a printer paper that can host more document pages on the same side. The feature can be enabled shipment by shipment by means of a user-defined boolean attribute.

> Warning

The extra pages will only be generated if the first page is currently in the wrong position, if the user-defined boolean attribute is "true" and if the feature is enabled.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Option**

**Description**

**Enable skipped pages**

Enables the evaluation of skipped pages.

**Pages per print sheet side**

Number of document pages that can be printed on a single printer paper sheet. Currently, maximum two pages per side are supported.

**Start shipment on page**

The position on the printer page that must be activated if the feature is triggered.

**if the following attribute value is true:**

A user-defined boolean attribute that enables the feature, evaluated at each shipment.

### PDF security
This feature allows to manage PDF security, requiring a password to allow operations.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Option**

**Description**

**Require a password to open the document**

Select this checkbox to enable a password to restrict access to the document. To set the password required to open the document, drag the desired password attribute into the corresponding field.

> Note

If the password is null or empty, access will be not restricted.

**Set restrictions and require password to allow operations**

Select this checkbox to enable a password to restrict operations on the document. To set the password required to perform operations on the document, drag the desired password attribute into the corresponding field.

> Note

If the password is null or empty no restrictions will be applied.

**Allow**

Select the allowed operations:

- **Printing **

- **Editing **

- **Copying**

- **Annotation editing**

**Allowed attributes**

Define the available attributes by dragging them into the corresponding field.

> Note

For more information, see: Managing Attributes.

### Encryption and packaging
This feature allows to manage encryption and packaging of the output.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Option**

**Description**

**Enable packaging**

Select this checkbox to enable the creation of a package.

**One package**

Select the preferred option to manage the creation of the package:

- **for every shipment **

- **for every spool file**

**Source path**

Set the source path of the package by dragging an attribute into the corresponding field.

**Output filename**

Set the package name by dragging an attribute into the corresponding field.

**Enable encryption**

Select this checkbox to enable encryption of the package.

**Password**

Set the encryption password.

**Require a password for open the archive**

Select this checkbox to set a password to open the archive by dragging an attribute into the corresponding box.

### Generate
This feature allows to manage the spool page generation.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Option**

**Description**

**Generate**

Select the preferred page generation option:

**all pages**

**only front pages**

**Generate spool file header**

Select this checkbox to enable the generation of an empty header page for each spool file.

**Generate spool file trailer**

Select this checkbox to enable the generation of an empty trailer page for each spool file.

## Modifying the properties of spool files
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

The actions described below apply to the **Spool files **section of the view.

- Access the spool set indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click the name of the spool set whose properties you wish to modify or **Single lot **if you have only one spool set.

- Drag a String type attribute into the **Path **field.

- Drag a String type attribute into the **Name **field.

- Drag a String type attribute into the **Index path **field.

> Warning

A file name must be supplied for each spool set.

### Creating a spool set or spool file index
- Access the spool set indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click the name of the spool set whose properties you wish to modify, or Single lot if you have only one spool set.

- Click &nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,) to create a new index.

- Enter a code for the index in the **New index **window.

- From the **Level **drop-down menu, select whether the index is to be a "spool set" or "spool file" index . If an index category was selected when the creation request was made, it will also be selected in the **Level **menu.

- Indicate whether this index must be created as a physical index or if the corresponding information must be added to the spool as TLE tags.

> Warning

This latter option is only available when the spool file is of AFP type.

- Click **New **or press **Enter **to confirm the creation and close the window.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Warning

The index creation window performs a validation on the code entered. If the code field is empty or is the same as another code already used in the Serializer, creation is not possible.

### Modifying the properties of a spool set or spool file index
![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Access the spool set indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click the name of the spool set whose properties you wish to modify or **Single lot **if you have only one spool set.

- Click the name of the index you wish to modify.

- Indicate whether this index must be created as a physical index (**Placed in a separate file**) or if the corresponding information must be added to the spool as TLE tags (**Placed inside the spool (AFPDS or PDF only)**). If you select to place the index **inside the spool (AFPDS or PDF only)**, the **Type **option appears.

- Enter the text of choice for the **Name**.

- Drag a String type attribute into the **File name **field.

- Select **Enable **to enable the Index.

- Set the encoding of the index file. The possible options are **UTF-8 **or **ANSI**.

- If in step 4. you selected to place the index **inside the spool (AFPDS or PDF only)**, set the **Type **option. The possible values are: **TLE**, **NOP **and **Bookmark (PDF only)**.

> Note

TLE and NOP are specific to AFPDS, while Bookmark can only be selected for PDFs.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

  If you select the **Bookmark **index type, the **Hierarchical **option appears.

- Select **Hierarchical **to make the index hierarchical.

> Note

Hierarchical indexes contain shipment events at the top; for each shipment, document events are added as children, producing a structure similar to a book index with chapters and paragraphs.

> Warning

A file name must be supplied for each index.

### Modifying the code of a spool set or spool file index
- Access the spool set indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click the name of the spool set whose properties you wish to modify or **Single lot **if you have only one spool set.

- Click the name of the index you wish to modify.

- Click **Change **next to the **Identifier **field.

- Enter a code for the configuration in the **Change index **window.

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

- Click **Apply **to confirm the change and close the window.

> Warning

The index modification window performs a validation on the code entered. If the code field is empty or is the same as another code already used in the Serializer, the change is not possible.

### Deleting a spool set or spool file index
- Access the spool set indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click the name of the spool set whose properties you wish to modify or **Single lot **if you have only one spool set.

- Click the name of the index you wish to delete.

- Click &nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,) to delete the index.

- In the confirmation prompt window, click **Delete **to confirm the operation and close the window.

## Spool set or spool file index occurrences
### Creating an occurrence for a spool set or spool file index
- Access the spool set indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click the name of the spool set whose properties you wish to modify or **Single lot **if you have only one spool set.

- Click the name of the index to which you wish to add an occurrence.

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) 	to add the occurrence.

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

- In the **Create occurrence **window, select the event on which you wish to set the occurrence from the **Event **menu:

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

- Click **Create **or press **Enter **to confirm the creation and close the window.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Warning

No more than one occurrence can be created on each index for each event available. If you have already created one or more occurrences, their events will no longer be available when additional occurrences are created for the same index.

### Deleting an occurrence for a spool set or spool file index
- Access the spool set indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click the name of the spool set whose properties you wish to modify or **Single lot **if you have only one spool set.

- Click the name of the occurrence you wish to delete.

- Click &nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,) to delete the occurrence.

- In the confirmation prompt window, click **Delete **to confirm the operation and close the window.

### Creating a record for a spool set or spool file index
- Access the Print Job indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click the name of the spool set whose properties you wish to modify or **Single lot **if you have only one spool set.

- Click the name of the occurrence to which you wish to add a record.

- Click &nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,) to add the record.

### Modifying the properties of a record for a spool set or spool file index
**![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

- Access the Print Job indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click the name of the spool set whose properties you wish to modify or **Single lot **if you have only one spool set.

- Click the name of the record whose properties you wish to modify.

- Enter the text of choice for the **Name**.

- Select the record terminator from the **Terminator **menu.

- Select the concatenation mode of the operands entered in the record from the **Concatenation **options **fixed length **and **variable length**

- If you wish to enter a separator between the operands in the record, enter the corresponding text in the **Separator **box.

 If you wish to use constant elements in the record, click the **Constant **button to add them, then click the corresponding box to modify the text.

-  If you wish to use variable elements in the record, drag them straight from the allowed attributes panel into the position required. 

-  If you wish to delete an element from the record, click the name of the element then click **Delete operand**.

-  If you wish to change the order of the elements in the record, drag them into the order required.

- Select **Enabling **to enable the index record based on the value of a boolean attribute. In the **Value **column of **Values **table, you can see the value of the operands in the record.

### Deleting a record for a spool set or spool file index
- Access the Print Job indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click the name of the spool set whose properties you wish to modify or **Single lot **if you have only one spool set.

- Click the name of the record you wish to delete.

- Click &nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,) to delete the record.

> Warning

No confirmation is required for the deletion of a record.
